gomodel:SYNGO_4519  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 9: \"PRAF2 is expressed in post and presynaptic terminals of the VTA.\"\n\"A, B, PRAF2 immunoperoxidase staining is present in axosomatic contacts. PRAF2 is readily detected as a dark amorphous, diaminobenzidine (DAB) reaction product, staining the vesicles ... and mitochondria enclosed in the axon terminal.\"\n\"Gold particles labeling in axon terminals ... contacting neuronal soma (H) or dendrite (I).\"\n\"Both asymmetric (Fig. 9A, B, D, F, G) and symmetric (Fig. 9C, E) synapses were stained, suggesting that PRAF2 is expressed in excitatory and inhibitory synapses.\". Experimental description: Anatomical and ultrastructural study of PRAF2 expression in the mouse central nervous system (Title of the paper)\n\nPRAF2 antibody (ARP American Research Products, Massachusetts, USA, JM4/PRAF2, #L166), an affinity-purified rabbit polyclonal antiserum raised against amino acid residues 165-178 of PRAF2 (p.4171)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" ;
        dc:date           "2023-10-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4519" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

